a) for female Italian voice, violin and piano\nBULLET::::- \"What Shall I Buy You, Son?\" (2000) for voice, piano\nBULLET::::- \"Boodschappenlijstje van een gifmengster\" (2000) (text by the composer) for vocalist (also writes), voice (may be performed as Shopping List of a Poisoner [translated by Nicoline Gatehouse]\nBULLET::::- \"Inanna's Descent\" (2000) for mezzo-soprano, piccolo, oboe, violin, piano, 2 percussion ensembles (4–12 total players)\nBULLET::::- \"The New Math(s)\" (2000) (text by Hal Hartley) for soprano, transverse flute, violin, marimba, CD (music by Michel van der Aa), 2000 (film score; may be performed as a concert work)\nBULLET::::- \"Feli-citazione\" (2000) for piano\nBULLET::::- \"Passeggiata in tram in America e ritorno\" (2001) (text by Dino Campana) for female Italian voice, 3 trumpets, 3 trombones, electric guitar, electric violin, double bass, piano, percussion, 1998 (also version for voice, flute, horn, 3 trumpets, 3 trombones, amplified violin, double bass, piano\nBULLET::::- \"De vleugels van de herinnering\" (2001) (text by Larissa Tiginachvili [Dutch translation]) for voice, piano\nBULLET::::- \"Fanfare om te beginnen\" (2001) for 6 groups of horns\nBULLET::::- \"La Passione\" (2000–02) (text by Dino Campana) for female jazz voice, violin, small orchestra (7 winds, 7 brass, electric guitar, cimbalom, 2 pianos, synthesizer, 2 percussion, 3 violins, bass guitar)\nBULLET::::- \"Very Sharp Trumpet Sonata\" (2002) for trumpet\nBULLET::::- \"Tuin van Eros\" (Garden of Eros) (2002) for string quartet\nBULLET::::- \"Klokken voor Haarlem\" (Bells for Haarlem) (2002) for piano, celesta, synthesizer, vibraphone (+ glockenspiel)\nBULLET::::- \"Pupazzetti\" by Alfredo Casella, arranged by Louis Andriessen for ensemble in 2002–2003\nBULLET::::- \"Inanna\" (2003) texts by Hal Hartley, Theo J.H. Krispijn) for 4 voices, 3 actors, mixed chorus, contrabass clarinet, 4 saxophones, violin, film (by Hal Hartley)\nBULLET::::- \"Letter from Cathy\" (2003) 