el\" (Christiaan Andriessen's view on the river Amstel) (2009) for ensemble\nBULLET::::- \"Life\" (2009) for ensemble, with film by Marijke van Warmerdam\nBULLET::::- \"Anaïs Nin\" (2009/10) for singer, ensemble and film\nBULLET::::- \"La Girò\" (2011), for violin solo and ensemble\nBULLET::::- \"Mysteriën\" (2013), for orchestra\nBULLET::::- \"Tapdance\" (2013), concerto for percussion and large ensemble\nBULLET::::- \"Two way ticket\" (2014), for piano\nBULLET::::- \"Theatre of the World\" (2013–15), a 'grotesque stagework' in nine scenes (Libretto by Helmut Krausser)\nBULLET::::- \"Signs and Symbols\" (2016), for wind ensemble\nBULLET::::- \"The Only One\", song cycle written for soprano Nora Fischer, first performed in the Royal Albert Hall at the 67th BBC Prom of 2019 on 8 September 2019.\n\nBULLET::::- Adlington, Robert: \"De Staat\". Hants. (UK): Ashgate (2004).\nBULLET::::- Andriessen, Louis and Elmer Schonberger (trans. Jeff Hamburg): \"The Apollonian Clockwork: On Stravinsky\" Amsterdam: Amsterdam UP (reprint, 2006).\nBULLET::::- Everett, Yayoi Uno. \"The Music of Louis Andriessen\". Cambridge: Cambridge University Press (2006). .\nBULLET::::- Trochimczyk, Maja (ed.): \"The Music of Louis Andriessen\". London: Routledge (2002).\nBULLET::::- Zegers, Mirjam (ed.): Trans. Clare Yates. \"The Art of Stealing Time\". Arc Publications. .\n\nBULLET::::- Andriessen page at Boosey and Hawkes: biography, works list, recordings and performance search.\nBULLET::::- Andriessen's artist page and recordings on Nonesuch Records\nBULLET::::- Documentary: \"Andriessen on Andriessen\"\nBULLET::::- The London Sinfonietta's Andriessen biography page\nBULLET::::- Louis Andriessen in conversation with Robert Davidson\n"}
